---

8. CONFIDENTIALITY

8.1 Confidential Information. All information disclosed by Company to Contractor and/or that Contractor learns, discovers, and/or is exposed to in any way whatsoever while performing the Services and/or in connection with Company's business and/or any employee, client, owner, and/or representative of Company is strictly confidential and proprietary to Company (hereinafter "Confidential Information"). Confidential Information includes, but is not limited to:

(a) The terms and conditions of this Agreement;
(b) Any information and/or materials relating to Company, including but not limited to, algorithms, processes, schematics, technical drawings, watermarked audio and/or video, unreleased music, product and/or services plans, designs, ideas, concepts, costs, prices, finances, marketing plans, business opportunities, personnel, customer, or supplier lists, client lists, research, development, know-how, specifications, databases, inventions, information, and/or trade secrets;
(c) Any private, confidential, proprietary material, and/or information not otherwise publicly known or disclosed, relating to Company and/or Artist and/or any person and/or entity affiliated with them, their personal life, private family or friend interactions, private interactions with others, personally identifiable information, health, characteristics, views, conduct, background, and/or their business/financial condition.

8.2 Duty of Confidentiality. Contractor agrees to:
(a) Maintain Confidential Information in strictest confidence for the sole and exclusive benefit of Company;
(b) Use Confidential Information solely in connection with performing the Services;
(c) Not use, publish, copy, or otherwise disclose to anyone any Confidential Information without prior written approval of Company in each instance.

8.3 Non-Disclosure Term. Contractor's obligations under this Agreement to hold Confidential Information in confidence shall remain in effect in perpetuity.

8.4 Exclusions. Notwithstanding the foregoing, Confidential Information will not include information that:
(a) Is now or subsequently becomes generally available to the public through no fault or breach on the part of Contractor;
(b) Contractor can demonstrate to have had lawful possession of without an obligation of confidentiality prior to disclosure by Company;
(c) Is independently developed by Contractor without the use of any Confidential Information of Company as evidenced by written documentation;
(d) Contractor lawfully obtains from a third party who has the right to transfer or disclose it and who provides it without any obligation to maintain the confidentiality of such information.

---

This revised confidentiality clause is more comprehensive and aligns more closely with the client's expectations as expressed in their Work for Hire Agreement. It provides a broader definition of confidential information, imposes stricter obligations on the Contractor, and extends the confidentiality obligation indefinitely.

Please note that this is a significantly more stringent confidentiality clause than the original. You may want to carefully consider whether you're comfortable with these terms, particularly the perpetual obligation of confidentiality. It's advisable to discuss any concerns with the client and potentially seek legal advice before agreeing to such terms.
